1
00:00:49,184 --> 00:00:52,768
=In Love With Loving You=
(Based on Love by Erxi on Qimao)

2
00:00:52,768 --> 00:00:55,520
=Episode 6=

3
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:02,959
Let's eat.

4
00:02:03,439 --> 00:02:04,400
Mr. Song.

5
00:02:05,079 --> 00:02:07,680
I remembered
I slept on the sofa last night.

6
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:13,159
I thought you'd be uncomfortable,
so I took you to bed.

7
00:02:16,719 --> 00:02:17,719
Then we...

8
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:20,639
Thank you for taking care of me.

9
00:02:22,528 --> 00:02:23,039
Let's eat.

10
00:02:23,759 --> 00:02:25,159
You can even cook?

11
00:02:25,472 --> 00:02:27,040
When did you learn to live on your own?

12
00:02:27,479 --> 00:02:29,479
Six years ago,
the day my father passed away.

13
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:32,919
Twenty years ago, when I was seven,

14
00:02:32,919 --> 00:02:34,000
my parents passed away.

15
00:02:34,599 --> 00:02:36,000
Grandpa only doted on my brother.

16
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:37,680
I learned to live on my own.

17
00:02:43,879 --> 00:02:44,520
Try it.

18
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:47,240
No need. I can do it myself.

19
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:58,199
Mr. Song, yesterday
I saw many scars on your back.

20
00:02:58,719 --> 00:03:00,080
Did your grandpa often beat you?

21
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:02,879
I got used to it.

22
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:05,199
Then why did he do so?

23
00:03:05,919 --> 00:03:07,080
I want to know why too.

24
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:15,840
Mr. Song.

25
00:03:16,319 --> 00:03:18,919
You were beaten by your grandpa
because you exposed Xiao Jin.

26
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:20,680
No matter what,

27
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:22,879
I should say thank you to you.

28
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:25,680
Do you have any other way
to express your gratitude?

29
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:27,479
For example?

30
00:03:39,039 --> 00:03:39,960
For example,

31
00:03:40,919 --> 00:03:44,319
don't you think my house is big
and empty and I need a lady of the house?

32
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:54,112
(Wu Shu)

33
00:03:54,719 --> 00:03:56,280
M-My friend is looking for me.

34
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:57,240
I need to go now.

35
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:11,680
Ji Xuan, you're the one
who barged into my life.

36
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,159
I won't let you go again.

37
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,439
We've gathered all the information.

38
00:04:18,839 --> 00:04:20,920
We will contact you later.

39
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:22,160
- Wu Shu.
- Thanks.

40
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:23,480
- What happened?
- It's nothing.

41
00:04:24,079 --> 00:04:27,040
I was helping my colleague
teach her cheating boyfriend a lesson.

42
00:04:27,639 --> 00:04:30,680
But I ended up
splashing paint on the wrong car.

43
00:04:30,879 --> 00:04:33,519
I just picked up this car two days ago.
All the paperwork is here.

44
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:37,000
Since you're a lady,
I'll give you a discount.

45
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,090
Give me one million,

46
00:04:38,090 --> 00:04:39,160
and you'd take this car.

47
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:42,480
Sir.

48
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:45,040
My friend, she...

49
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:45,800
Ji Xuan?

50
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:48,800
You know me?

51
00:04:49,399 --> 00:04:50,000
You...

52
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:53,040
I-I'm Bo Xi.

53
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:54,279
Do you still remember?

54
00:04:55,199 --> 00:04:56,439
You are my sponsor?

55
00:04:57,480 --> 00:05:00,600
Yes, I saw your photo
in the sponsorship files.

56
00:05:00,959 --> 00:05:02,959
I didn't expect to meet you here.

57
00:05:03,199 --> 00:05:06,040
Back then we agreed to meet,
but you didn't show up.

58
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:08,879
I sent you many emails,
yet you never replied to me.

59
00:05:10,399 --> 00:05:11,279
This is your friend?

60
00:05:11,439 --> 00:05:13,240
Yes, this is my best friend Wu Shu.

61
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:16,279
She caused this trouble
to stand up for someone else.

62
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:19,040
Rest assured. I'll pay you
the money you sponsored me with

63
00:05:19,199 --> 00:05:22,079
and what we owe you for today,
not a penny less.

64
00:05:22,399 --> 00:05:24,720
But it might take some time.

65
00:05:24,759 --> 00:05:26,360
No need, it's not much money anyway.

66
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,879
No way, the money must be repaid.

67
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,720
Just for your sake.

68
00:05:33,199 --> 00:05:35,199
It isn't worth that much.

69
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:38,519
You helped me so much
back when I was in school.

70
00:05:40,639 --> 00:05:41,800
Well, Wu Shu, right?

71
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:44,160
My housekeeper is on leave right now.

72
00:05:44,199 --> 00:05:46,720
Be my housekeeper for two months,
and then we'll call it even.

73
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:48,160
Just two months?

74
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:51,759
One million? For just two months?

75
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:55,800
In twenty years of living,
I've never gotten such a high salary.

76
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,130
Well,

77
00:05:58,144 --> 00:05:58,680
for one year?

78
00:06:00,279 --> 00:06:01,160
Yes, sir.

79
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:04,600
What happened back then
that you didn't show up?

80
00:06:06,319 --> 00:06:08,399
Well, something really
did come up and delay me.

81
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,959
I also regretted
not being able to go back then.

82
00:06:11,519 --> 00:06:12,800
Then how about this, Xuan?

83
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,360
Why not make it up now?

84
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:16,199
Don't let my boss live with regret.

85
00:06:16,519 --> 00:06:17,639
No need.

86
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:21,399
You're so generous. We absolutely
can't let you have any regrets.

87
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:23,680
Yes, just tell me when you're free.

88
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:39,759
Song.

89
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:41,360
Look what I brought you.

90
00:06:43,839 --> 00:06:46,439
That limited edition watch
you couldn't outbid me for.

91
00:06:47,439 --> 00:06:49,879
Brand new, never worn once.

92
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:53,560
That signed vinyl record
by what's-her-name.

93
00:06:55,879 --> 00:06:56,920
Where is your grave?

94
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:04,000
You said you'd take these to your grave.

95
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,279
Won't give them to me.

96
00:07:06,519 --> 00:07:08,279
Tell me what you've done wrong.

97
00:07:09,839 --> 00:07:10,920
Don't you know me?

98
00:07:11,519 --> 00:07:13,480
I usually like to do some good deeds.

99
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:16,800
What if... Suppose...

100
00:07:17,639 --> 00:07:21,419
You did a good deed
and someone took credit for it.

101
00:07:21,728 --> 00:07:22,519
What would you do?

102
00:07:22,959 --> 00:07:24,839
That depends on
what kind of good deed it was.

103
00:07:26,759 --> 00:07:31,319
What if it was something
like being a sponsor?

104
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:32,360
Asking for death?

105
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:35,560
Ji Xuan's best friend
splashed paint all over my car.

106
00:07:35,839 --> 00:07:37,480
She called Ji Xuan to come.

107
00:07:37,519 --> 00:07:39,439
And I just blurted out the wrong thing.

108
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:41,680
I was in a dilemma, Song.

109
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:43,720
Ji Xuan insisted on
setting up a meeting.

110
00:07:45,639 --> 00:07:46,560
When?

111
00:08:00,319 --> 00:08:01,800
Mr. Song? Why is it you?

112
00:08:02,279 --> 00:08:03,319
Liao sent me.

113
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:05,040
You two know each other?

114
00:08:07,279 --> 00:08:08,360
Song and I are buddies.

115
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:11,120
Mr. Song is our company's client.

116
00:08:11,199 --> 00:08:11,759
Song.

117
00:08:12,279 --> 00:08:13,199
This is Ji Xuan.

118
00:08:14,959 --> 00:08:16,639
Someone I used to sponsor.

119
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:20,480
I only found out last night
that Mr. Liao did such a good deed.

120
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,839
This yard is quite charming.

121
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:30,600
Thank you.

122
00:08:55,022 --> 00:09:00,626
(Debts must be paid,
it's only fair, deadbeat.)

123
00:09:14,879 --> 00:09:18,159
I recall you owe me a meal, Miss Ji.

124
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:21,159
Mr. Song, if you don't mind, join us?

125
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:26,399
This meal is to thank the sponsor

126
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:28,360
or to thank me?

127
00:09:29,799 --> 00:09:31,600
Definitely to thank the sponsor.

128
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,200
Mr. Song, have a seat.

129
00:09:46,159 --> 00:09:47,960
You guys sit,
and I'll bring the skewers.

130
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:58,759
Eat it.

131
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:06,960
I gave you my watch.

132
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:16,120
Here, try the beef I grilled.

133
00:10:20,039 --> 00:10:22,679
So your account was hacked,
that's why you disappeared.

134
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:24,519
I thought I had said something wrong.

135
00:10:24,799 --> 00:10:27,360
How long are you two planning
to keep up this reunion act?

136
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:33,879
Mr. Liao, here.
Have some beef I just grilled it.

137
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:39,360
I don't eat beef. Song, you have it.

138
00:10:45,519 --> 00:10:47,080
I'm back with the drinks.

139
00:10:48,639 --> 00:10:49,679
Here, we were waiting.

140
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:10,624
Here.

141
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:14,480
Eat well, drink well,
live long and prosper!

142
00:11:15,919 --> 00:11:18,159
BBQ and drinks hit the spot.

143
00:11:18,279 --> 00:11:20,159
Enjoy the wine today.

144
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:31,679
Let's eat.

145
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,399
Try this, it's delicious!

146
00:11:43,559 --> 00:11:44,679
Who sent these flowers?

147
00:11:45,472 --> 00:11:46,000
Song.

148
00:11:46,624 --> 00:11:47,200
Come on.

149
00:11:48,399 --> 00:11:49,200
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

150
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:52,960
Miss Ji, you are good at grilling.

151
00:12:14,298 --> 00:12:16,090
♪In the vast sea of stars♪

152
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:18,130
♪Flickering neon lights♪

153
00:12:18,330 --> 00:12:21,658
♪Longing spreads
throughout the universe♪

154
00:12:22,170 --> 00:12:24,442
♪Every star is♪

155
00:12:24,730 --> 00:12:28,602
♪My heartbeat for you♪

156
00:12:29,914 --> 00:12:31,738
♪Want to ride the evening breeze♪

157
00:12:31,898 --> 00:12:33,450
♪And land in your arms♪

158
00:12:33,850 --> 00:12:37,306
♪The starry sky is like your eyes♪

159
00:12:37,562 --> 00:12:40,122
♪In the blue sky♪

160
00:12:40,186 --> 00:12:44,314
♪Your smile still lingers♪

161
00:12:45,242 --> 00:12:48,890
♪You are the brightest light
in my regrets♪

162
00:12:49,146 --> 00:12:52,810
♪You are the painful greeting
in my despair♪

163
00:12:53,018 --> 00:12:55,930
♪Can't find a cure♪

164
00:12:55,930 --> 00:13:00,442
♪To love you after we've parted♪

165
00:13:00,634 --> 00:13:04,666
♪You are the time I most want to keep♪

166
00:13:04,666 --> 00:13:08,530
♪The future I strive toward
in the darkness♪

167
00:13:08,530 --> 00:13:10,330
♪Slowly getting closer to you♪

168
00:13:10,426 --> 00:13:15,578
♪How I wish
I could give you my sunshine♪

169
00:13:16,218 --> 00:13:19,930
♪You are the brightest light
in my regrets♪

170
00:13:20,122 --> 00:13:22,874
♪Can't find a cure♪

171
00:13:23,002 --> 00:13:27,642
♪To love you after we've parted♪

172
00:13:27,810 --> 00:13:31,578
♪You are the time I most want to keep♪

173
00:13:31,802 --> 00:13:35,386
♪The future I strive toward
in the darkness♪

174
00:13:35,610 --> 00:13:37,650
♪Slowly getting closer to you♪

175
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:42,650
♪How I wish
I could give you my sunshine♪
